      "file_path": "packages/policy-clamp-tarball/src/main/resources/etc/logback_element.xml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 27,
      "message": "I think this is toobroad on debug mode for this top level package as it captures many subpackages, etc .. I think, may be remove?  I am of the opinion of that default log level should be info max, they should be overwritable in a deployment with the logback.xml override that you have in the previous file .sh.   In addition, you could have added to the configuration element on top a watcher to detect log level changes in the file, so will do it automatically if changed, see for example logback.xml in core components, pap, etc .. for an example.",
